1
00:00:04,220 --> 00:00:07,270
KOBAYASHI Kaoru

2
00:00:19,008 --> 00:00:22,058
KUROTANI Tomoka

3
00:00:38,620 --> 00:00:41,670
LILY Franky

4
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,020
ODAGIRI Joe

5
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:59,390
- Found him!
- He's here...

6
00:00:59,820 --> 00:01:01,840
It's him...

7
00:01:03,590 --> 00:01:05,740
Don't resist!

8
00:01:09,460 --> 00:01:11,080
("Shinjuku's largest gambling operations
prosecuted... Operators arrested for
profitting from gambling..")

9
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:11,760
("Arrested suspect, Katagiri")

10
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:13,710
On that night, 8 years ago...
("Arrested suspect, Katagiri")

11
00:01:13,710 --> 00:01:14,460
("Arrested suspect, Katagiri")

12
00:01:14,460 --> 00:01:16,780
Time seemed to have stopped for him.
("Arrested suspect, Katagiri")

13
00:01:16,780 --> 00:01:17,420
("Arrested suspect, Katagiri")

14
00:01:19,222 --> 00:01:22,222
Directed by: MATSUOKA Joji

15
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,110
He had lost everything.

16
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:28,420
Still clenching firmly to the seeds of hope...

17
00:01:29,311 --> 00:01:33,611
...sealed up along with his bitter memories.

18
00:01:50,574 --> 00:01:56,174
SHINYA SHOKUDO (Season 2)
'The Late-Night Diner'

19
00:02:11,584 --> 00:02:17,184
Master... Another glass of ginger ale
plus garlic gyoza please.

20
00:02:17,850 --> 00:02:19,880
Comin right up.

21
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:22,080
Delivery?

22
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:29,760
Hello?
Can you still make a delivery to 'Meshi'-ya?

23
00:02:34,690 --> 00:02:36,030
Thanks for the patronage.

24
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:36,700
Hello.

25
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:39,800
Sorry... For troubling you to come
here during your closing time.

26
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,860
No problem.

27
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:46,100
We can accomodate orders up to 1 am,
but since our daughter is still small...

28
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,980
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

29
00:02:49,620 --> 00:02:52,560
Also this...
I made this chili oil myself so please use it.

30
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,130
Really?

31
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:56,980
Thanks then, I'll accept it.

32
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:58,830
Thanks for your patronage.

33
00:02:58,830 --> 00:03:00,500
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

34
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:16,090
This really tastes awesome...

35
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:20,130
But Master...
didn't you make your own gyoza before?

36
00:03:20,390 --> 00:03:24,790
Yeah.
But I'd rather eat these than make em.

37
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:27,380
So I just call to have them delivered.

38
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:31,460
In Kamata, Tokyo, particularly in the Haneda
area, the gyoza there is famous.

39
00:03:32,930 --> 00:03:37,270
That owner who delivered this...
was trained in a Chinese restaurant in Haneda.

40
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,720
He had dreamed of opening
his own store...

41
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,490
Now he finally opened one nearby.

42
00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:48,130
It's true... so yummy!

43
00:03:48,130 --> 00:03:50,120
Isn't it?

44
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:03,910
I'll do the rest, you can go now.

45
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,240
Just one more.

46
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:11,380
'Just one more...just one more...'
you've been saying that for the past 3 minutes.

47
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,140
I guess so.

48
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,680
It's okay.

49
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:20,240
It's faster if two people are doing this.

50
00:04:24,930 --> 00:04:26,990
Hey, you've stopped...

51
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:30,950
Uh, yes.

52
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:54,640
Hey, Master... still not here yet?

53
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,590
I'll call and ask them.

54
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,120
Sorry! Thank you for waiting.

55
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:06,610
- It's here!
- Finally!

56
00:05:07,570 --> 00:05:10,900
At last, we'll be able to eat
the legendary gyoza.

57
00:05:12,050 --> 00:05:14,240
- Where's the owner today?
- Should I place this here?

58
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,910
- Yup!
- Yes.

59
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:20,480
We had a lot of deliveries today...

60
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,470
...so instead...

61
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:25,230
...my husband entrusted me
to deliver this.

62
00:05:25,650 --> 00:05:27,700
Is that so...
Oh, here.

63
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:30,560
Take this.

64
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:35,140
Thank you for your patronage.

65
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,540
Til next time.

66
00:06:22,316 --> 00:06:24,376
Why was she delivering the food?

67
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:32,110
I was surprised myself... I didn't know she's
the wife of the gyoza store owner.

68
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:41,540
Do you remember 8 years ago?

69
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:50,930
<i>He's late, huh?</i>

70
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:57,390
<i>Today is my birthday.</i>

71
00:06:59,670 --> 00:07:04,320
<i>I'm getting impatient because he called me
up and told me to wait here...</i>

72
00:07:06,770 --> 00:07:10,440
<i>And that at exactly 12 midnight,
he'd give me a ring.</i>

73
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:16,180
<i>Guess he's a man who
can't keep his promises.</i>

74
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:21,590
<i>I actually believed him.</i>

75
00:07:24,730 --> 00:07:27,870
Better stop thinking of foolish things.

76
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:36,560
I just want my life back.

77
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:39,430
Don't get into that anymore.

78
00:07:41,650 --> 00:07:46,310
Those times, it's already over
between you and her.

79
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:51,840
These past eight years...

80
00:07:53,036 --> 00:07:55,296
...it was the same for her too, but...

81
00:07:56,115 --> 00:07:58,335
...she had chosen to embark on
a different road.

82
00:08:02,136 --> 00:08:04,446
From hereon as well.

83
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:11,300
It is shameful but...
can't it really be helped?

84
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:20,200
Good evening.

85
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,100
Welcome.

86
00:08:52,601 --> 00:08:54,281
Master.

87
00:08:55,509 --> 00:08:57,939
You're very satisfied with our gyoza, right?

88
00:08:58,982 --> 00:09:00,982
Yeah.

89
00:09:01,620 --> 00:09:04,030
But you can make it, too...

90
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:07,560
...so that when our store's closed...

91
00:09:07,940 --> 00:09:10,560
...you can still serve gyoza
to your customers.

92
00:09:11,430 --> 00:09:15,050
Yours is better... I can't make
it as good as your gyoza.

93
00:09:15,780 --> 00:09:18,430
Don't worry about it, Master.

94
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:24,160
My wife's birthday is next week.

95
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:26,620
Our store will be closed.

96
00:09:27,089 --> 00:09:28,485
Really?

97
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:33,460
It was a second marriage for me.

98
00:09:34,330 --> 00:09:37,370
My daughter is my child
from my ex-wife.

99
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:42,270
But my wife is really
good to my daughter.

100
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:48,000
Master, my daughter has always
wanted to come here.

101
00:09:48,230 --> 00:09:50,240
I would like to bring my wife.

102
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:54,620
I'll teach you to make gyoza, and
in exchange, you celebrate her birthday with us.

103
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,200
But no need for a gift.

104
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,510
Just being with us is fine.

105
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,920
Sure thing.

106
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:08,310
Four orders of fried gyoza.

107
00:10:08,310 --> 00:10:10,350
Yep.

108
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:16,230
Thank you for calling,
this is Anomori Gyoza Store...

109
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:20,930
Yes.

110
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:23,530
Yes.

111
00:10:25,310 --> 00:10:27,310
Is it a delivery?

112
00:10:28,770 --> 00:10:30,720
A call from my home.

113
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:36,840
My father said that he'll continue
working at the factory...

114
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:39,520
I have to see him tomorrow.

115
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:42,890
Okay...
You should persuade him not do it.

116
00:10:44,645 --> 00:10:45,820
Yes.

117
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,440
I also didn't know you got arrested.

118
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,810
Later on, my dad became ill...

119
00:11:14,819 --> 00:11:17,579
I had to constantly watch over
him at the hospital.

120
00:11:24,532 --> 00:11:26,942
I thought you had abandoned me.

121
00:11:30,223 --> 00:11:32,243
I thought the same about you.

122
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:37,790
Although I haven't forgotten you...

123
00:11:38,555 --> 00:11:40,725
... I had no time to worry about it.

124
00:11:46,242 --> 00:11:51,785
Afterwards, my father was discharged from
the hospital, and a little while later...

125
00:11:51,810 --> 00:11:57,710
I had a marriage meeting with him...
...and married him.

126
00:12:01,264 --> 00:12:03,404
You have a child?

127
00:12:04,730 --> 00:12:09,630
We have a daughter...
she's in elementary school.

128
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:14,200
And you?

129
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:25,890
Your birthday's coming soon.

130
00:12:31,020 --> 00:12:32,990
Can I still fulfill that promise I made to you?

131
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,480
Let's go somewhere together.

132
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,120
Stop joking!

133
00:12:42,850 --> 00:12:44,600
That's already a thing of the past.

134
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:52,260
I thought I'd never see you again.

135
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:55,750
So I erased from my memories
those times that I spent with you.

136
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:00,430
What's wrong with that?

137
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:05,080
I would never have thought of you
if we didn't meet again.

138
00:13:08,610 --> 00:13:11,150
I better go back soon...

139
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,410
Please stop.

140
00:13:16,744 --> 00:13:21,553
At 7 pm, on the night of your birthday,
I'll be waiting for you outside the diner.

141
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:16,520
<i>The snow that fell yesterday
has not melted...</i>

142
00:14:17,580 --> 00:14:22,310
<i>Seldom lasted this long...
it still remained on her birthday.</i>

143
00:14:26,114 --> 00:14:28,144
Master.

144
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:31,280
I know how you got your scar.

145
00:14:31,601 --> 00:14:34,741
- Asuka.
- Tell me how I got it.

146
00:14:35,311 --> 00:14:37,491
You got hit by a yoyo.

147
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:39,770
I also hit Kaoru-chan with it
and blood came out.

148
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:42,060
But soon, she got better.

149
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:45,460
I'm really sorry.
She's fond of speaking out of turn.

150
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:52,490
Papa, guess what I'm doing.

151
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:54,380
- It's a bit shoddy.
- What is it?

152
00:14:55,650 --> 00:14:57,610
It's really lousy.

153
00:14:58,140 --> 00:14:59,784
Is it a croissant?

154
00:14:59,784 --> 00:15:01,399
Correct!

155
00:15:04,730 --> 00:15:09,540
Master.
My parents have never quarreled.

156
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:11,900
They really have a good relationship.

157
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:14,552
- Lovey-dovey, huh?
- That's right, super lovey-dovey.

158
00:15:17,180 --> 00:15:20,550
- Huh? Where is it?
- What's wrong?

159
00:15:21,140 --> 00:15:24,350
Just the recipe for the chili oil
I wrote for Master...

160
00:15:24,850 --> 00:15:27,300
It seems I forgot to bring it.

161
00:15:27,690 --> 00:15:31,030
- Never mind, just give it next time.
- It's okay, I'll go and get it.

162
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:36,070
Papa, can I go with you, too?

163
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:37,980
- Sure, come on.
- Yay!

164
00:15:38,060 --> 00:15:40,020
Let's go.

165
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,220
- There's still snow.
- Yeah.

166
00:15:44,290 --> 00:15:46,100
Likely there'll be more.

167
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:48,050
Asuka.

168
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,760
We're off then.

169
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:08,720
Be careful while walking.

170
00:16:08,820 --> 00:16:10,830
- We'll be back soon.
- Be back soon.

171
00:16:11,950 --> 00:16:14,610
Oh, I saw some snow crystals.

172
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:18,590
- How did you see it?
- Tachibana-sensei showed it to us in school.

173
00:16:18,590 --> 00:16:20,040
- Through a microscope?
- Yes.

174
00:16:40,380 --> 00:16:42,720
It seems it's not so simple.

175
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:51,580
The gyoza I wrapped... is in good
competition with Asuka-san's.

176
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:56,390
I was also poor in wrapping gyoza at first.

177
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,180
My husband would often scold me for it...

178
00:17:00,730 --> 00:17:03,360
He wanted to let you know...

179
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,720
That this is his passion.

180
00:17:11,660 --> 00:17:13,680
I know.

181
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,050
Master.

182
00:17:18,610 --> 00:17:21,290
Do you want to say that I should
continue living happily?

183
00:17:26,660 --> 00:17:28,620
But it's impossible to go back to the past!

184
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:32,180
Are you going?

185
00:17:39,110 --> 00:17:42,220
Your life... it doesn't only belong to you.

186
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:49,840
My life...
belongs to me.

187
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:33,660
Mama.

188
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:39,010
Mama, happy birthday.

189
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:44,080
- How did you get this?
- It's a secret we kept from you.

190
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:46,090
We reserved a cake for you
and we went to pick it up.

191
00:18:47,510 --> 00:18:52,060
- We wanted to surprise you.
- Oh, I'll show it to Master.

192
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:00,930
I...

193
00:19:35,270 --> 00:19:37,580
You might catch a cold.

194
00:19:48,115 --> 00:19:51,826
Mama, let's cook the gyoza.

195
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:57,100
Okay.

196
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:14,420
<i>He didn't show up in my diner anymore.</i>

197
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:31,500
- Here you go.
- Looks delicious!

198
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:36,760
Itadakimasu.

199
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:49,160
- Yum!
- So good.

200
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:56,230
~Watashi no umareta kono machi wa ~
*I was born in this city*

201
00:20:57,140 --> 00:21:02,430
~ Taitei konkuriito de dekite ite ~
*Mostly made with concrete*

202
00:21:02,910 --> 00:21:08,580
~ Tonari no kojo kara wa kikai no oto ga kikoeru ~
*Always hear the sound from the next-door factory*

203
00:21:08,580 --> 00:21:13,130
At the end of the day, people are rushing home...
~ Tonari no kojo kara wa kikai no oto ga kikoeru ~
*Always hear the sound from the next-door factory*

204
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:15,030
~ Watashi to ittara mukiryoku de ~
*I'm a person always without any energy*

205
00:21:15,030 --> 00:21:17,680
But if you also feel something's left unfinished...
~ Watashi to ittara mukiryoku de ~
*I'm a person always without any energy*

206
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,160
~ Watashi to ittara mukiryoku de ~
*I'm a person always without any energy*

207
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,140
Some nights, you may want to make a detour.
~ Watashi to ittara mukiryoku de ~
*I'm a person always without any energy*

208
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:21,770
Some nights, you may want to make a detour.
~ Sora bakkari nagamete ita ~
*Looking only at the sky*

209
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:25,330
~ Sora bakkari nagamete ita ~
*Looking only at the sky*

210
00:21:25,780 --> 00:21:31,340
~ Tori no uta mo kikoenai foroo o ~
*I cannot hear the birds singing*

211
00:21:31,550 --> 00:21:35,570
~ Kikai wa utatte ita ~
*The machines were singing*

212
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:47,450
~ Son'na machi ga watashi no furusato ~
*Such is my hometown*

213
00:21:50,580 --> 00:21:58,890
~ Subete no dekigoto wa itoshii omoi de ~
*All things are cherished memories*

214
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:10,090
~ Son'na machi ga watashi no furusato ~
*Such is my hometown*

215
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:22,370
~ Kikai no oto wa natsukashii komori uta ~
*Sounds of machines, nostalgic lullabies*

216
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,650
Welcome.

217
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:33,380
If I can, I'll make you anything you like.

218
00:22:35,650 --> 00:22:39,700
=Shinya Shokudo (Season 2)=
The End.

219
00:22:39,850 --> 00:22:46,450
~ Yarusenai yuhi yori ~
*More than the dreary sunset*

220
00:22:40,950 --> 00:22:43,450
<i>'Master'
KOBAYASHI Kaoru</i>

221
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:46,400
<i>   'Murata'               'Momoko'
LILY Franky      KUROTANI Tomoka</i>

222
00:22:46,650 --> 00:22:53,470
~ Shinji reru asahi o mitai ~
